Absolutely not!

I think you are confused about installing

  - R (ie the interpreter, or engine)
  - R packages from the distribution
  - R packages directly from CRAN

I have worked with that very mix for what must now be over fifteen years
(from when we starting to package r-cran-*) and it just works. I tend to do
mostly 1) and 3) to update R packages more quickly then the distribution
might but that is mostly a personal preference.

This list is good for sortiing these questions out so please continue to post
til you feel you got it working.

